  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The FISBe dataset represents a significant advancement in the instance segmentation of long-range thin filamentous structures. Available on Zenodo, this dataset has achieved 955 views and 1,084 downloads, indicating a healthy engagement from the research community.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The FISBe dataset, published in 2024 and hosted on Zenodo, establishes a critical benchmark for the instance segmentation of thin filamentous structures. This dataset, developed by prominent institutions\u2014including the Janelia Research Campus at the Howard Hughes Medical Institute, the Max Delbr\u00fcck Center, and the German Cancer Research Center\u2014reflects a collaborative effort aimed at addressing complex challenges in this area of research.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">With a total of 955 views and 1,084 downloads reported on Zenodo, the FISBe dataset demonstrates strong engagement and interest from the scientific community, underscoring its relevance and utility. These metrics can be indicative of a dataset considered valuable for future research endeavors in the field of computer vision and biological imaging.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The authors' commitment to open science is underscored by their practice of early sharing, as indicated by the dataset's early sharing/preprint status. Although no preprint downloads or citations have been reported, the act of sharing this dataset pre-publication exemplifies a proactive approach to nurturing community engagement and collaboration.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, the FISBe dataset stands as a foundational research output that promotes active research in the instance segmentation of biological structures. Its availability on a prominent data repository like Zenodo provides the scientific community with a valuable resource that can facilitate ongoing research and technological advancements in this specialized field.</p>",
